										<footer class="article-contributor contributors">
									

<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Ron Jones</strong></span> lives in San Francisco, California, where he teaches at the San Francisco Recreation Center for the Handicapped, and writes. His latest book, <em>Shared Victory, A Collection of Unusual World Records</em> ($4.50 from Ron Jones, 1201 Stanyan St., San Francisco, Ca. 94117) records &ldquo;gallant imagination and cooperative effort&rdquo; among his students in such activities as &ldquo;tallest inner tube sandwich,&rdquo; &ldquo;most catchers of a tennis ball with a fishnet,&rdquo; &ldquo;longest human conveyor belt,&rdquo; and so on. It&rsquo;s a delight.</p><a href="/contributors/ron-jones" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

							</footer>
						</article>


